The Police Command in the Federal Capital Territory (FCT) has arrested a 43-year-old man for allegedly defiling his 15-year-old daughter in Lugbe area of Abuja. The Commissioner of Police in FCT, Mr Bala Ciroma, at a media briefing in Abuja, said the suspect was mentally stable and confessed to having carnal knowledge of his daughter on several occasions. Ciroma added that 12 suspects in connection to kidnapping activities were also arrested around Bwari, Abaji and Kwali axis of Abuja. Seventeen rounds of live ammunition, four dane guns, one locally made pistol and four mobile phones were recovered from the suspects. Other recovered item are two military camouflage uniform and caps, one motorcycle, five voterâ€™s cards and two sim-packs and cards. Ciroma added that the suspects would be charged to court on completion of investigations.